        <descriptionSet>
            <description>A card sent from Filippo Galante to Enrico Caruso in 1903. The Miscellaneous category of cards, which this card belongs to, represent the oddities among the cards. They depict children playing with a tea set or the seedy side of "Le Notte."  Some of these cards might also be considered humorous, although the image alone is not sufficient for a modern observer to know. The miscellaneous category demonstrates the diversity of the cards collected and published.</description>
